Aelian Historical RIisveZlanies : When the poet Pindar competed at Thebes he happened on ignorant judges, and was defeated five times by Corinna. By way of exposing their lack of good taste, he called Corinna a sow.1

Pausanias Description of Greece: Corinna, the only poet of Tanagra, is commemorated by a monument in the open street and by a painting in the gym- nasium. The latter represents her in the act of putting on the headband she won when she defeated Pindar in the lyric competition at Thebes.
